Heat George Foreman Grill or panini maker. Top 4 slices of bread evenly with cheese, ham and tomato slices. Top with remaining slices of bread. Mix dressing and mustard together. Spread tops of sandwiches with mixture. Place dressing-side down on grill. Spread tops of sandwiches with remaining dressing mixture. If not all sandwiches fit easily, cook in batches. Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread is golden brown and crisp.